Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
ICONIC BUILDING REDEVELOPMENT

CBRE is pleased to present ‘The Marina Picture Palace’ – 405-409 Gardeners Road, Rosebery. This mixed use development site has been DA approved for 36 luxury residential units and 5 ground floor retail shops. The property offers developers and investors the opportunity to transform this historically significant site into an iconic apartment block by way of the DA, or venture to return the building to its former glory as a theatre, accommodation or creative space in one of Sydney’s most vibrant centres.

‘The Marina Picture Palace’ capitalises on the following key attributes: 

- Land area: 1,088sqm*
- DA approved for 36 residential units and 5 retails shops
- Versatile B1 Neighbourhood Centre zoning
- Ideal for a variety of uses (accommodation, cinema, or creative space)
- Formerly an iconic movie theatre, beginning operations in 1927
- Buses to the Sydney CBD available directly outside property
- 850m* from Rosebery’s renowned food district
- 4.7km* from Sydney CBD
- Located closely to the University of New South Wales, University of Sydney and the Prince of Wales Hospital
- Only a short distance to the Eastern Beaches including Coogee, Clovelly and Maroubra
- Young professional and tertiary student demographic
- High performing residential suburb in Sydney’s inner fringe

*Approximate

Benefiting from elevated foot and road traffic this 134sqm* strata property is surrounded by an abundance of amenity.

Property highlights:

• 134sqm* of open plan floor area
• 15sqm* exclusive courtyard
• Suitable for creative office, retail, showroom 
• Mechanical ventilation and grease trap suitable for food users
• Saw tooth roof with high ceilings
• Bathed in natural light with floor to ceiling windows
• Prominent ground floor corner location
• Extensive Botany Road frontage
• Secure basement parking and storage
• Dual street entrances for customers
• Situated in the booming Rosebery precinct
• Offered with vacant possession
• 1km* from Green Square Station
